definition.value: A member of the class of quinazolines that is quinazolin-4(3H)-one in which the hydrogens at positions 2 and 3 are replaced by 1-{4-[(4-chlorophenoxy)acetyl]piperazin-1-yl}ethyl and 2-ethoxyphenyl groups, respectively. It is an inhibitor of voltage-dependent anion-selective channels (VDAC2 and VDAC3) and a potent ferroptosis inducer.

A 2-amino-4-(S-butylsulfonimidoyl)butanoic acid which has S-configuration. It is a inhibitor of gamma-glutamylcysteine synthetase and glutathione (GSH) biosynthesis and is capable of enhancing the apoptotic effects of several chemotherapeutic agents.
A methoxyisoflavone that is  isoflavone substituted by a methoxy group at position 6 and hydroxy groups at positions 5, 7 and 4' respectively.
A nitrile that is benzonitrile which is substituted by chlorines at positions 2 and 6. A cellulose synthesis inhibitor, it is used as a pre-emergent and early post-emergent herbicide.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (Z)-(1R)-cis-tefluthrin and (Z)-(1S)-cis-tefluthrin.

A member of the class of indolones that is 1,3-dihydro-2H-indol-2-one substituted by hydroxy, 2-(4-methoxyphenyl)-2-oxoethyl, chloro, and chloro groups at positions 3, 3, 4, and 7, respectively. It blocks RNA helicase A binding to EWS-FLI1, induces apoptosis, and exhibits antineoplastic activity.
A biphenyl that is substituted by a {8-[4-(pyridin-3-yl)-1H-1,2,3-triazol-1-yl]octanoyl}amino group at position 2.
